<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2026 09:22:06 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>This New Year, 12 people lost a hand through firework injuries</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/this-new-year-12-people-lost-a-hand-through-firework-injuries/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261793 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-fireworks category-new-year"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> This New Year, 12 people lost a hand through firework injuries</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-04T09:22:06+00:00"> January 4, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-207794" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_207794"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Depositphotos_497426438_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-207794"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="181" data-start="0">Plastic surgeons treated 93 people for serious fireworks injuries around New Year, a sharp rise on last year‚Äôs total of 62, the<span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal"> Dutch plastic surgeons‚Äô association said at the weekend.</span></span></p><p data-end="590" data-start="183">The association said many of the injuries were severe and involved young victims, with serious injuries often caused by illegal fireworks. At least 12 people lost a hand.</p><p data-end="590" data-start="183">Surgeons also treated numerous finger amputations, fractures and tendon damage, frequently combined with burns and serious facial injuries. About 75% of patients required surgery.</p><p data-end="590" data-start="183"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="806" data-start="592">In almost all cases, the injured person had set off the fireworks themselves, with only 10 patients identified as bystanders. Roughly three-quarters of the injuries were linked to illegal fireworks and more than two-thirds of the 93 patients were aged 18 or younger, the association said.</p><p data-end="1349" data-start="1039"><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Rotterdam‚Äôs eye hospital</span></span> also reported an unusually high number of minors with fireworks-related injuries.</p><p data-end="1349" data-start="1039">About 85% of its patients were under 18, compared with around half in previous years. The youngest patient treated was five years old. Almost all of the eye injuries involved bystanders.</p><p data-end="1349" data-start="1039"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="1349" data-start="1039">This was the last New Year in which consumers could buy legal, more powerful fireworks and a ban on letting of fireworks had already been imposed in 20 towns and cities, including Amsterdam.</p><p data-end="1349" data-start="1039">Nevertheless, the ban was widely ignored everywhere it was in force.</p><p data-end="279" data-start="107">The number of cars and homes catching fire during this year‚Äôs New Year festivities also far outstripped last year‚Äôs figures, according to the public safety institute NIPV.</p><p data-end="417" data-start="286">This year the emergency services were called out to 361 car and 228 home fires, compared with 270 and 144 respectively in 2025.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/fireworks/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/new-year/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261793</guid><pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2026 09:22:06 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Snow set to continue until Tuesday, more flights cancelled</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/snow-set-to-continue-until-tuesday-more-flights-cancelled/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261785 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-schiphol category-society category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Snow set to continue until Tuesday, more flights cancelled</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-04T08:52:29+00:00"> January 4, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-261786" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_261786"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="672" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546253507.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546253507.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546253507-560x376.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546253507-768x516.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-261786"> Snow at the Loonse en Drunense Duinen national park. Photo: Iris van den Broek ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="303" data-start="107">A code yellow weather warning remains in force for the entire Netherlands on Sunday and will remain in place until Tuesday because of freezing conditions, the KNMI weather bureau said on Sunday.</p><p data-end="478" data-start="310">There was heavy overnight snow in places on Saturday night and more snow is expected in the coming days, although coastal areas are not expected to be badly affected.</p><p data-end="683" data-start="485">The snow has led to several accidents on the roads and more delays at Schiphol airport.</p><h2 data-end="683" data-start="485">Flights scrapped</h2><p data-end="683" data-start="485">KLM has cancelled 295 services on Sunday and warns that flights which are going ahead are subject to delays. More than 200 flights were scrapped on both Friday and Saturday.</p><p data-end="754" data-is-last-node="" data-start="690">Meanwhile, social media is full of photos of snowy gardens, parks and vistas. Here are some of the highlights.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="nl">Zondagmorgenwandeling in de bossen van Hoenderloo. Overal een betoverend uitzicht. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/sneeuw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#sneeuw</a> <a href="https://t.co/r0S7ZdDzhR">pic.twitter.com/r0S7ZdDzhR</a></p><p>‚Äî Maarten Molenaar (@maartenmiller) <a href="https://twitter.com/maartenmiller/status/2007731558371995772?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">January 4, 2026</a></p></blockquote><p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="nl">Wat was <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Deventer?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Deventer</a> gisteravond prachtig. Het <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/sneeuw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#sneeuw</a> zorgde voor een sprookjesachtig effect. Ik kon het dan ook niet laten om een mooie avond wandeling te maken.<br/> Wat een voorrecht heb ik toch om in deze mooie stad te wonen. ‚õÑÔ∏è‚ùÑÔ∏èüíö<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Winterweer?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Winterweer</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Sneeuwfoto?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Sneeuwfoto</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Winter?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Winter</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Hanzestad?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Hanzestad</a> <a href="https://t.co/ST4nSI8Blj">pic.twitter.com/ST4nSI8Blj</a></p><p>‚Äî Jeffrey Ó®Ä (@WillemsJeffrey) <a href="https://twitter.com/WillemsJeffrey/status/2007732829632033033?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">January 4, 2026</a></p></blockquote><p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="nl">Molen in sneeuwlandschap in Aarlanderveen ZH. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Sneeuw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Sneeuw</a><br/> Gem. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/AlphenaandeRijn?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#AlphenaandeRijn</a>. <a href="https://t.co/KQrUSyzePb">pic.twitter.com/KQrUSyzePb</a></p><p>‚Äî Gert-Jan (@GWemeyer) <a href="https://twitter.com/GWemeyer/status/2007734324041527645?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">January 4, 2026</a></p></blockquote><p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="nl">Mijn achtertuin!üò≥<a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/sneeuw?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#sneeuw</a> <a href="https://t.co/4CQZs7pz8g">pic.twitter.com/4CQZs7pz8g</a></p><p>‚Äî ‚öíJo van der Heijden‚öí (@WHUFC_Helmond) <a href="https://twitter.com/WHUFC_Helmond/status/2007734670813995447?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">January 4, 2026</a></p></blockquote><p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/schiphol/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261785</guid><pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2026 08:52:29 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Football, skating, cricket, hockey: 2026‚Äôs sporting calendar</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/football-skating-cricket-hockey-2026s-sporting-calendar/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261771 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-amsterdam category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Football, skating, cricket, hockey: 2026‚Äôs sporting calendar</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-04T08:22:56+00:00"> January 4, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-254233" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_254233"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1494" sizes="(max-width: 2100px) 100vw, 2100px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic.jpg 2100w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic-560x398.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic-1200x854.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic-768x546.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic-1536x1093.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/SCO-vs-NED-team-pic-2048x1457.jpg 2048w" width="2100"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-254233"> The Netherlands in action in Scotland last year. Photo: Ian Jacobs/Cricket Scotland</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="279" data-start="135">The Winter Olympics, the football World Cup and a series of major championships in the Netherlands will make 2026 a busy year for sports fans.</p><p data-end="685" data-start="286">The international calendar is dominated by the Winter Olympics in Italy running from February 6 to 22, followed later in the year by the football World Cup in North America.</p><p data-end="685" data-start="286">The Netherlands will also be represented at the men‚Äôs T20 World Cup cricket tournament, which starts on February 7 in India and Sri Lanka.</p><p data-end="685" data-start="286"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="1018" data-start="859">The football World Cup runs from June 11 to July 19 in the United States, Canada and Mexico. The Dutch national team opens its campaign on June 14 in Dallas.</p><p data-end="1424" data-start="1134">Then in August, the hockey World championships take place in the Netherlands and Belgium between August 15 and 30. The Wagener Stadium in Amstelveen will host the Dutch arm of the competitions and the women‚Äôs final.</p><p data-end="1424" data-start="1134"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="1424" data-start="1134">At the same time, the world rowing championships will take place on the nearby¬† Bosbaan rowing course from August 24 to 30.</p><p data-end="1424" data-start="1134">Zandvoort also hosts what is expected to be the final Dutch Formula 1 Grand Prix on August 23.</p><p data-end="1604" data-is-last-node="" data-start="1431">Top-level sport continues into the autumn, with the world gymnastics championships in Rotterdam in October, alongside the Amsterdam Marathon and European cyclo-cross events.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261771</guid><pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2026 08:22:56 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>No world darts title for Gian van Veen as Luke Littler wins 7-1</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/no-world-darts-title-for-gian-van-veen-as-luke-littler-wins-7-1/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261779 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-darts category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> No world darts title for Gian van Veen as Luke Littler wins 7-1</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-04T08:21:03+00:00"> January 4, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-261781" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_261781"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546294187.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546294187.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546294187-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546294187-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546294187-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-261781"> England's Luke Littler (right) and Gian van Veen after the match. Photo: AP Photo/Dave Shopland</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Dutch darts player Gian van Veen was unable to make his dream of a first PDC World Championship title a reality on Saturday night, losing 7-1 to English teenager Luke Littler in the final.</p><p>‚ÄúIt is difficult to have lost, especially by 7-1,‚Äù said Van Veen after the game at Alexandra Palace in London. ‚ÄúI can get angry and frustrated but the better man won.‚Äù</p><p>Van Veen won the first set and gave Littler a tough time in the second but had nothing more to give as the competition progressed. Nevertheless, he picked up 400,000 pounds sterling in prize money.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p data-end="472" data-start="328">The match had been dubbed the ‚Äúyoungest final ever‚Äù, given the combined age of the two participants was just 41.</p><p data-end="678" data-start="479">If he had won, Van Veen would have come home one million pounds sterling richer and would have been the third Dutch PDC world champion ever, after Michael van Gerwen (2014, 2017, 2019) and Raymond van Barneveld (2007).</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/darts/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261779</guid><pubDate>Sun, 04 Jan 2026 08:21:03 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dutch Caribbean islands on alert after US Venezuela strikes</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/dutch-caribbean-islands-on-alert-after-us-venezuela-strikes/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261772 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-airlines category-caribbean category-foreign-affairs"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutch Caribbean islands on alert after US Venezuela strikes</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-03T13:39:51+00:00"> January 3, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-261773" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_261773"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="570" sizes="(max-width: 777px) 100vw, 777px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kaart_van_Essequibo_Grensconflict_Venezuela_Guyana-e1767447545759.png" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kaart_van_Essequibo_Grensconflict_Venezuela_Guyana-e1767447545759.png 777w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kaart_van_Essequibo_Grensconflict_Venezuela_Guyana-e1767447545759-560x411.png 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kaart_van_Essequibo_Grensconflict_Venezuela_Guyana-e1767447545759-768x563.png 768w" width="777"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-261773"> Map: SurinameCentral via Wikimedia Commons</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="322" data-start="107">Dutch caretaker prime minister Dick Schoof on Saturday assured the Caribbean islands of Aruba, Cura√ßao and Bonaire that they could count on Dutch support following the US military attack on neighbouring Venezuela.</p><p data-end="527" data-start="329">The islands are between 35 and 80 kilometres from the coast of Venezuela, where US armed forces carried out raids in the early hours of Saturday morning and took president Nicolas Maduro and his wife prisoner.</p><p data-end="731" data-start="534">Schoof <a href="https://x.com/MinPres/status/2007411657480323123">said on social media</a> he had spoken with the leaders of Aruba and Cura√ßao and the governor of Bonaire to underline that ‚Äúthey and the people on the islands can count on our support in this uncertain time‚Äù.</p><p data-end="731" data-start="534"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="731" data-start="534">Aruba and Cura√ßao are independent countries within the kingdom of the Netherlands, while Bonaire has local authority status.</p><p data-end="1993" data-start="1687">The US operates counter-narcotics aircraft from two <a href="https://www.southcom.mil/Commanders-Priorities/Counter-Threats/Cooperative-Security-Locations/">bases on Cura√ßao and Aruba </a>under agreements signed in 2000 and 2001.</p><p data-end="1993" data-start="1687">In December, when asked about the US strikes on boats which the US claimed to be moving drugs, defence minister Ruben Brekelmans said these facilities had not been used in the attacks.</p><p data-end="1993" data-start="1687"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="1993" data-start="1687">Brekelmans has not yet commented on the latest attacks on Venezuela.</p><p data-end="1076" data-start="851">Earlier, the foreign affairs ministry urged Dutch nationals in Venezuela to get in touch with family and friends and let them know they are all right. The country has been subject to a code red no-travel warning since July.</p><p data-end="1315" data-start="1083">KLM has reportedly <a href="https://www.bonaire.nu/nieuws/luchtvaart-reizen/84188/klm-momenteel-geen-vluchten-naar-bonaire-curacao-aruba-en-sint-maarten">cancelled all flights</a> to Cura√ßao, Aruba and Sint Maarten following the US attacks on Venezuela. The Dutch flag carrier has also cancelled flights to Georgetown in Guyana and Bridgetown on Barbados.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/airlines/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/caribbean/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/foreign-affairs/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261772</guid><pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2026 13:39:51 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dutchman Gian van Veen sets his sights on world darts title</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/dutchman-gian-van-veen-sets-his-sights-on-world-darts-title/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261767 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-darts category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutchman Gian van Veen sets his sights on world darts title</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-03T10:11:32+00:00"> January 3, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-261768" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_261768"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546203524.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546203524.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546203524-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546203524-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546203524-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-261768"> Gian van Veen celebrates winning his semi-final match against Gary Anderson. Photo: Credit Image: ¬© Ian Stephen/Action Plus Sports via ZUMA Press Wire</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="321" data-start="107">Darts player Gian van Veen has become only the third Dutch player ever to take part in a PDC World Championship final, after beating two-time world champion Gary Anderson 6‚Äì3 in the semi-finals on Friday evening.</p><p data-end="472" data-start="328">Van Veen, who is 23, will meet 18-year-old Luke Littler in the final on Saturday evening. The match has been dubbed the ‚Äúyoungest final ever‚Äù, given the combined age of the two participants is just 41.</p><p data-end="678" data-start="479">Should he win, Van Veen will come home one million pounds sterling richer and will be the third Dutch PDC world champion ever, after Michael van Gerwen (2014, 2017, 2019) and Raymond van Barneveld (2007).</p><p data-end="678" data-start="479"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="868" data-is-last-node="" data-start="685">‚ÄúIf I win, perhaps Dutch youngsters will consider taking up the sport,‚Äù Van Veen told the AD. ‚ÄúAnd hopefully that will bring more Dutch players to the world championships in years to come.‚Äù</p><p data-end="868" data-is-last-node="" data-start="685">Van Veen and Littler <a href="https://www.skysports.com/darts/news/12028/13489777/luke-littler-vs-gian-van-veen-new-rivalry-takes-centre-stage-at-world-darts-championship-final-at-alexandra-palace">have met six times before</a> and are currently level pegging on wins.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/darts/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261767</guid><pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2026 10:11:32 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Travellers warned of more delays, cancellations at Schiphol</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/travellers-warned-of-more-delays-cancellations-at-schiphol/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261762 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-airlines category-schiphol category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Travellers warned of more delays, cancellations at Schiphol</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-02T19:01:56+00:00"> January 2, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-261763" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_261763"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="698" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546178124.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546178124.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546178124-560x391.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ANP-546178124-768x536.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-261763"> Schiphol was very busy on Friday. Photo: Koen van Weel ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Schiphol airport is warning that hundreds of flights are likely to be cancelled or delayed on Saturday because of the wintry weather.</p><p>The airport has urged¬†passengers to check their flight status before travelling to the airport, stressing that delays and cancellations could change at short notice. ‚ÄúThe situation is still developing,‚Äù a spokeswoman told broadcaster NOS on Friday evening..</p><p data-end="770" data-start="499">Snow showers and strong winds already caused widespread disruption on Friday and the wintry weather is expected to continue over the weekend.¬†Overnight temperatures will hover around freezing, allowing snow to settle and increasing the risk of icy roads.</p><p data-end="770" data-start="499"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="1365" data-start="1089">The disruption at Schiphol is being compounded by operational restrictions and the strong westerly winds mean only two runways can be used instead of the usual three.</p><p data-end="1644" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="1367">As a result, around 20 aircraft can land and 20 depart per hour, compared with up to 60 during peak periods under normal conditions.</p><p data-end="1644" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="1367">Flights to and from <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Eindhoven</span></span>¬†and <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Rotterdam airports</span></span> are not currently affected by the weather.</p><p data-end="1644" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="1367">The KNMI weather bureau has issued a code yellow weather warning for the entire country for the weekend because of the forecast snow and hail.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/airlines/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/schiphol/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261762</guid><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jan 2026 19:01:56 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>New Year celebrations marred by 361 car and 228 home fires</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/new-year-celebrations-marred-by-361-car-and-228-home-fires/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261760 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-fireworks category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> New Year celebrations marred by 361 car and 228 home fires</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-02T14:08:04+00:00"> January 2, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-228366" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_228366"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1920" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Discarded-fireworks-box-NYD-2023-2048x1536.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-228366"> Photo: Brandon Hartley</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="279" data-start="107">The number of cars and homes catching fire during this year‚Äôs New Year festivities has far outstripped last year‚Äôs figures, according to the public safety institute NIPV.</p><p data-end="417" data-start="286">This year the emergency services were called out to 361 car and 228 home fires, compared with 270 and 144 respectively in 2025.</p><p data-end="526" data-start="424">The national fire brigade said on Thursday it had been a busier year, with 4,286 call-outs in total.</p><p data-end="660" data-is-last-node="" data-start="533">The emergency services were prepared for a difficult evening, given this was the last time consumers can legally set off fireworks.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/fireworks/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261760</guid><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jan 2026 14:08:04 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Train passengers faced record number of disruptions in 2025</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/train-passengers-faced-record-number-of-disruptions-in-2025/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261743 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-public-transport category-railways category-trains"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Train passengers faced record number of disruptions in 2025</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-02T11:32:23+00:00"> January 2, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-173856" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_173856"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="450" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cancelled-Trains-at-Leiden-Centraal.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cancelled-Trains-at-Leiden-Centraal.jpg 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cancelled-Trains-at-Leiden-Centraal-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cancelled-Trains-at-Leiden-Centraal-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cancelled-Trains-at-Leiden-Centraal-130x98.jpg 130w" width="600"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-173856"> Photo: Brandon Hartley</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Dutch rail company NS clocked up a record number of disruptions to services in 2025, according to data from monitor<a href="https://www.rijdendetreinen.nl/statistieken"> Rijdendetreinen.nl</a>.</p><p>The site registered a total of 6,676 incidents, up almost 12% compared to 2024 and 4,000 up from 2011, when records started.</p><p>The average extra waiting time for passengers was 167 minutes. The longest disruption was recorded on the track between Maastricht and Luik when no services were available at all from April 8 to April 29 due to a strike by Belgian train staff.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Most of the disruptions took place in January, with 600 taking place during the morning rush hour.</p><p>Rotterdam central station topped the list with 900 incidents, closely followed by Schiphol airport and Breda. The majority of disruptions were caused by broken-down trains.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/public-transport/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/railways/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/trains/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261743</guid><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jan 2026 11:32:23 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Wintry weather spells cancellations and delays at Schiphol</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/01/wintry-weather-spells-cancellations-and-delays-at-schiphol/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-261748 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-schiphol-2 category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Wintry weather spells cancellations and delays at Schiphol</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-01-02T10:52:31+00:00"> January 2, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-183969" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_183969"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="450" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Empty-KLM-Departures-Area.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Empty-KLM-Departures-Area.jpg 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Empty-KLM-Departures-Area-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Empty-KLM-Departures-Area-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Empty-KLM-Departures-Area-130x98.jpg 130w" width="600"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-183969"> Photo: Brandon Hartley</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Some 200 flights have been cancelled and hundreds have been delayed because of wintry conditions at Schiphol airport.</p><p>The airport has urged people travelling on Friday to check the most<a href="https://www.schiphol.nl/nl/berichten/2-januari-kans-op-vertragingen-en-annuleringen-door-winters-weer/"> recent flight information</a> before setting out.</p><p>Delays are likely to pile up during the day, a Schiphol spokesman told broadcaster NOS. ‚ÄúWintry showers and the direction of the wind are disrupting the frequency with which planes can land or take off one after the other,‚Äù he said.</p><p>Flights from Eindhoven airport and Rotterdam/The Hague airport have not been affected so far.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/schiphol-2/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=261748</guid><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jan 2026 10:52:31 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>